8.01	Rack_(torture_device)	Rack (torture)	The rack is a torture device consisting of a rectangular, usually wooden frame, slightly raised from the ground, with a roller at one, or both, ends, having at one end a fixed bar to which the legs were fastened, and at the other a movable bar to which the hands were tied. The victim's ankles are fastened to one roller, and the wrists are chained to the other.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/A_Torture_Rack.jpg/200px-A_Torture_Rack.jpg
